11 SECTION 2. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
12 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 6060.51 of Title 36, unless
13 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
14 A. An enrollee may choose to pay for a health care service out-
15 of-pocket from a licensed health care provider. If an enrollee
16 negotiates for a lower cost from a licensed health care provider
17 than the average allowed amount paid by the carrier to a network
18 provider for a comparable health care service, and the enrollee pays
19 for the health care service out-of-pocket, the enrollee may send
20 documentation, which may be sent electronically, to the carrier,
21 that provides the following:
22 1. The health care service the enrollee or patient received and
23 the licensed health care provider's name and contact information;
24
